---
interface Props {
  yearsExperience: number;
}

const { yearsExperience } = Astro.props;
---

<section id="about" class="py-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-12 text-center">
            <span class="bg-gradient-to-r from-violet-400 to-cyan-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent">About Me</span>
        </h2>
        <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center">
            <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mb-6 text-lg">
                From Cordoba, Argentina to Utah, USA
            </p>
            <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                I'm running <a href="https://vulktech.com" target="_blank" class="text-violet-400 hover:text-violet-300 transition-colors font-medium">Vulktech</a>, a software factory helping startups and businesses ship their ideas faster. Currently also building <a href="https://kazend.com" target="_blank" class="text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 transition-colors font-medium">Kazend</a> for real estate, with more products in the queue.
            </p>
            <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                I believe great software starts with clean code â€” readable, maintainable, and built to last. But not at the cost of shipping. No endless roadmaps, no over-engineering. Just build, ship, iterate.
            </p>
            <p class="text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed mb-8">
                When I step away from the keyboard, you'll find me chasing clear skies in a 172 or chasing match points on the tennis court.
            </p>
            <div class="flex justify-center gap-6">
                <div class="bg-zinc-900 px-8 py-4 rounded-xl border border-zinc-800">
                    <div class="text-3xl font-bold text-violet-400 mb-1">{yearsExperience}+</div>
                    <div class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">Years Building Software</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
